        <prompt>What was the major focus of the 14th Amendment to the Constitution?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Granting citizenship and equal protection under the law</option>
            <option letter="b">Abolishing slavery</option>
            <option letter="c">Guaranteeing voting rights</option>
            <option letter="d">Establishing income tax</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The 14th Amendment, ratified in 1868, granted citizenship to all persons born in the US and guaranteed equal protection under the law.</explanation>
