        <prompt>What role did the Union League play during Reconstruction?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Organized African Americans politically and provided mutual aid</option>
            <option letter="b">Represented former Confederate interests</option>
            <option letter="c">Operated as a secret military organization</option>
            <option letter="d">Managed Northern business investments</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Union League helped organize African Americans politically, provided mutual assistance, and helped establish schools and churches in black communities.</explanation>
