    <question>
        <prompt>What was "carpetbagger" a derogatory term for during Reconstruction?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Northerners who moved South after the Civil War</option>
            <option letter="b">Southern Republicans who supported Reconstruction</option>
            <option letter="c">Former Confederate soldiers</option>
            <option letter="d">Freedmen's Bureau agents</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>Southerners used "carpetbagger" as a derogatory term for Northerners who moved South after the Civil War, suggesting they carried all their belongings in carpetbags.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
        <prompt>What was the purpose of the Ku Klux Klan Act of 1871?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">To suppress Klan violence and protect African American rights</option>
            <option letter="b">To establish public schools in the South</option>
            <option letter="c">To regulate interstate commerce</option>
            <option letter="d">To organize military districts</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Ku Klux Klan Act authorized President Grant to use federal troops to suppress Klan violence and protect African Americans' civil rights.</explanation>
